               <head>Grant; Wissett, etc.; 4 Ed. II (1310-1311)</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Hobert</forename> 
                           <surname>Dilhegges</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105585">Wissett (Wyssete)</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  grants to the <persName>lady <forename>Petronilla</forename> de <surname>Nerford</surname>
                        </persName> 
                  and her heirs, a capital messuage in <placeName key="place_105585">Wissett (Wyssete)</placeName> with arable lands, woods, fields,
                  &amp;c. which he has in the villages of Wyssete, <placeName key="place_105471">Rumburgh</placeName>,
                  <placeName key="place_105499">Spexhall (Spectishale)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105322">Halesworth (Halesworthe)</placeName> and <placeName key="place_105352">Holton</placeName>
                  
                  supplying him with sustenance during his life and half a mark yearly for shoes.
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_105585">Wissett (Wyssete)</placeName> the
                  Wednesday next before the feast of St. Mark the evangelist, <origDate notBefore="1310-07-08" notAfter="1311-07-07">4 Ed. II</origDate>.
                   
                  </p>
